com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.swing

Class PSwingPropertyUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.swing.PSwingPropertyUtils

  • public final class PSwingPropertyUtils
extends Object
    Collection of static methods to store and retrieve global properties. These methods act as a replacement for those in AppContext, as they are part of the Java non-public API. A separate map of key-value pairs are available for each top-level ThreadGroup. As some Java experts now consider ThreadGroup to be most obsolete, it is used here only as a convenient mechanism to separate threads from different application contexts. (Reference)

    Normally, in Swing applications, it is not safe to use mutable static members, as multiple Java apps can run simultaneously from the same Java Virtual Machine. Instead, mutable global properties should be managed with this class. To be clear: It is not necessary to use this class to store truly immutable properties: final primitives or final references to final class instances.

    Quoting this reference: A Swing application is not necessarily run by its own Java Virtual Machine. Applets or webstart applications placed on the same html page may share one JVM, which leads to the common static data. A static field changed by one application may unexpectedly affect another application.

    To improve performance, MRU (most recently used) caching is employed.

    Author:
    Kevin Connor ARPE (kevinarpe@gmail.com)

    • Method Detail

      • get

        @FullyTested
public static Object get(Object key)
        Retieves the value associated with key for the current thread's top-level group. These values may never be null, so a return value of null always indicates key is unmapped. This behavior is different from some implementations in JDK that allow for null keys and values, such as HashMap.

        In practice, it may be better to use getAndPutIfMissing(Object, com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.FuncUtils.Func0) to handle when key is unmapped, so a value must be created and inserted. All this is done in a thread-safe setting.

        This method is thread-safe and replaces AppContext.get(Object).

        Parameters:
        key - a key to look-up. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        associated value or null to indicate key is unmapped
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if key is null
        See Also:
        getAndPutIfMissing(Object, com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.FuncUtils.Func0), put(Object, Object), remove(Object), Thread.getThreadGroup(), AppContext.get(Object)

      • getAndPutIfMissing

        @FullyTested
public static Object getAndPutIfMissing(Object key,
                                    com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.FuncUtils.Func0<Object> createValueFunc)
        Similar to get(Object), but if key is unmapped, create the value by calling functor createValueFunc, then insert a new key-value pair.

        This method is thread-safe (including calling functor createValueFunc) and replaces AppContext.get(Object).

        Parameters:
        key - a key to look-up. Must not be null.
        createValueFunc -
        • functor to create value if key is unmapped
        • must not be null
        • if functor is invoked, must not return null
        Returns:
        associated value. Never null
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if key or createValueFunc is null
        IllegalStateException - if functor createValueFunc is invoked and returns null
        See Also:
        get(Object), put(Object, Object), remove(Object), AppContext.get(Object)

      • put

        @FullyTested
public static Object put(Object key,
                     Object value)
        Associates value with key for the current thread's top-level group. If an existing mapping exists for key, it is replaced.

        This method is thread-safe and replaces AppContext.put(Object, Object).

        Parameters:
        key - must not be null
        value - must not be null. If weak reference is necessary, see WeakReference.
        Returns:
        null is no previous mapping, else previous associated value
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if key or value is null
        See Also:
        get(Object), getAndPutIfMissing(Object, com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.FuncUtils.Func0), remove(Object), Thread.getThreadGroup(), AppContext.put(Object, Object)
